pageContext.claim: “Do you remember I used to say that people made more money 21 years ago? All of the time and they had one job then they did -- this is two, three years ago, right, than they did working two and three jobs now.”
pageContext.analysis: The percentage of people with two or more jobs has been around 5 percent for almost a decade. There has been virtually no change since 2016, when Trump was campaigning for president, and 2019.
